Eight people were injured after a taxi crashed into a roadside barrier on the N3 southbound highway near the Richmond Road in Marrianhill, KwaZulu-Natal on Monday.The taxi was found facing oncoming traffic in the left lane of the highway and occupants were already out of the vehicle walking around on the scene.On arrival ER24 paramedics found that eight people had sustained minor to moderate injuries. Fortunately, no serious or fatal injuries were reported on the scene. And all eight were transported to R.K Khan Hospital for further treatment.It is understood that the driver lost control of the vehicle, causing it to crash into the barriers. Local authorities will be investigating further.-TNA Reporter 